SIMPLE: repass
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repass
<hw>Re*pass"</hw> <pr>(r?-p?s")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>pass</ets>: cf. F. <ets>repasser</ets>. Cf.
<er>Repace</er>.]</ety> <def>To pass again; to pass or travel over in
the opposite direction; to pass a second time; <as>as, to
<ex>repass</ex> a bridge or a river; to <ex>repass</ex> the
sea.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repass</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repass
<hw>Re*pass"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To pass or go back; to move
back; <as>as, troops passing and <ex>repassing</ex> before our
eyes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repassage</ent>⟦br⟧
